trend_summary: Across the series, forested pockets shrink as housing subdivisions and commercial/warehouse clusters fill gaps, especially along the main east-west corridor. New roads, parking lots and sports fields appear, expanding the impervious footprint yet leaving sizeable green tracts. Growth is steady but moderate, yielding a medium-density suburban landscape.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of detached-housing subdivisions on western and southeastern edges.
Expansion of large white-roof commercial/warehouse buildings near the northern arterial interchange.
Clearing of central forest patch for light-coloured pads and athletic fields.
Addition of new collector roads and roundabouts linking previously isolated cul-de-sacs.
Noticeable growth of parking lots around retail plazas in the north.
